Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease one 7x11 inch baking dish. In a large bowl, mix together the mushroom soup, sour cream, Monterey Jack and Colby cheeses. Combine the vegetables, water chestnuts, salt and pepper with the soup mixture. Stir together and pour into baking dish. Bake uncovered for 30 minutes. Remove from oven, top with onions and bake 10 minutes longer.